The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 8 centres shortlisted

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

Calcutta: The Board has shortlisted eight of the nine regular Test centres as venues for the 2011 World Cup ? not that the tournament has been awarded to Asia, but (the fresh) submission process is underway. 

According to The Telegraphs sources, the eight are (alphabetically): Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Calcutta, Chennai, Mohali, Mumbai, Nagpur and New Delhi. Because of regular problems, Kanpur has been excluded. 

One understands the Board has asked them to confirm, within a few days, that the mandatory requirements will be met. If theres a problem, then the ODI centres are going to come into the picture. 




